# AI Agent Context Standards

## Standard Context Files

This project provides standard context files that AI coding assistants automatically discover:

### Root-Level Files

| File | Purpose | Tool Discovery |
|------|---------|----------------|
| `AGENTS.md` | Primary AI agent instructions | Cursor, Claude Code |
| `CLAUDE.md` | Claude-specific instructions | Claude Code |
| `CONTRIBUTING.md` | Contribution guidelines | All tools |
| `ARCHITECTURE.md` | System architecture overview | All tools |
| `README.md` | Project overview | All tools |

### Tool-Specific Files

| File | Tool | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| `.github/copilot-instructions.md` | GitHub Copilot | Repository instructions |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Cursor | Glob-based rules |
| `.cursor/mcp.json` | Cursor | MCP server configuration |

## Context Hierarchy

1. **`AGENTS.md`** - Authoritative source of project guidelines
2. **Tool-specific files** - Reference AGENTS.md, add tool-specific hints
3. **`.cursor/rules/`** - Context-specific rules with glob patterns

## When Adding New Context

1. **Prefer updating existing files** over creating new ones
2. **Reference AGENTS.md** instead of duplicating content
3. **Keep tool-specific files minimal** - only add unique hints
4. **Add glob patterns** to `.cursor/rules/` for file-type specific guidance

